@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Login no autorizado (credenciales inválidas)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{adminUserName}}",
  "password": "ClaveIncorrecta"
}

### 2. Login usuario base (sin rol asignado; ver variables compartidas clienteUserName/clientePassword)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{clienteUserName}}",
  "password": "{{clientePassword}}"
}

### 3. Login admin (usa las variables compartidas adminUserName/adminPassword)
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{adminUserName}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}

### 4. Login recaudador
# Este usuario debe existir con el rol 'recaudador'
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "recaudador01",
  "password": "Recaudador123!"
}

### 5. Login root (usa las variables compartidas rootUserName/rootPassword)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "{{rootUserName}}",
  "password": "{{rootPassword}}"
}

### 6. Verificar token JWT
# Ejecuta primero "3. Login admin" en esta sesión; reutiliza ese token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAdmin.response.body.$.access_token}}
Accept: application/json

